subSubSection.paragraph:
The specimens bear zigzags of greater (
Fig. 23D
) or lesser amplitude (
Fig. 23I
). Some specimens bear a gradual transition from wavy lines to a zigzag pattern (
Fig. 23H, I
), while others show an abrupt transition, probably due to a growth interruption (
Fig. 23F, G
). Wavy axial lines crossing and forming a localized grid, called meshwork (
Fig. 23M, N
) as defined by 
Meinhardt (1998
: fig. 5.3c, d), have been observed too.

